  <ol class="questionList">
    <li id="q1">The proportion of men who were found guilty or cautioned in 2000 ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a1">declined steadily throughout the year.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a2">increased steadily with age.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a3">was greater than the proportion of women.</a></li></list></li>
	
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q2">In 2000 over 7 per cent of all ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a4">18-year-old males were offenders.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a5">male offenders were 18 years old.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a6">18-year-olds were offenders.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q3">In 2000 ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a7">more crimes were committed by 20-year-old women than by 30-year-old women.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a8">a greater percentage of 20-year-old women than 30-year-old women committed crimes.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a9">more 20-year-old women than 30-year-old women committed crimes.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q4">In 2000 ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a10">no one over the age of 70 was found guilty or cautioned.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a11">the number of 70-year-old offenders fell sharply.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a12">only a tiny proportion of people over the age of 70 were found guilty or cautioned.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q5">In 2000 approximately 0.5 per cent of ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a13">30-year-old offenders were women.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a14">30-year-old women were offenders.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a15">crimes were committed by 30-year-old women.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q6">Between 1999 and 2001 ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a16">there was an overall decrease in the number of recorded crimes.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a17">the overall number of recorded crimes remained the same.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a18">there was an overall increase in the number of recorded crimes.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q7">Between 1999 and 2001 there was a reduction in ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a19">only a few types of crime.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a20">most types of crime.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a21">all types of crime.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q8">Over the period 2000-2001 the total number of thefts, including car thefts, stood at just over ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a22">2,000.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a23">2 million.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a24">3 million.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q9">Over the period 2000-2001 ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a25">nearly half of all thefts involved motor vehicles.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a26">over half of all thefts were thefts of motor vehicles.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a27">the majority of thefts were thefts from vehicles.</a></li></list></li>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q10">Between 2000 and 2001 ...
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="a28">fewer people were arrested than between 1999 and 2000.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a29">fewer offenders were cautioned or found guilty than between 1999 and 2000.</a></li>
	<li><a id="a30">fewer crimes were recorded than between 1999 and 2000.</a></li></list></li>
